title: For Sale:  Interarms 50 Cal Hawken Rifle, High Quality
postcontent: First off, the quality on these is better than you are going to find on anything else. Unfortunately, our American companies like Thompson Center, Lyman, and Traditions are all producing cheaply made "traditional" muzzle loaders these days. The wood on those tends to have no grain or poor wood grain quality, and fit and finish is sloppy. Also they are using thinner brass on the furniture, and not finishing it out, especially on the patch boxes. On the Tradidtions I saw yesterday at Sportsman's Warehouse, the patch box is of minimum size, no depth to it, and bare wood on the inside, meaning no wood sealant was put on it to protect it from moisture, and the very thin brass door of the patch box certainly won't keep moisture out.  Call me, Jeff, at REDACTED, from 9am - 11pm. These Interarms Hawkens are SO MUCH BETTER in how they are made, everything is more sturdy, especially the brass furniture and wood quality. This one has a 29 inch , 66 twist barrel.  It has a very strong stock with good looking black mineral streaking lines that go down the full length of the stock. The buttstock is not skinny like on a lot of muzzle loaders at the local sporting goods stores. This normal thickness stock gives a wider footprint on your shoulder to mitigate recoil, meaning it will be a comfortable gun to shoot. The patch box is exceptional. It goes deep and has a lot of room for patches and primers, etc. It's not just decorative, it is every bit as functional as it is good looking, making it different and better than a lot of guns of this type. The brass furniture is excellent on this rifle, and so is the double set trigger. The sights are very good too. They are easy to use and practical in lower light. The only flaw is there are a few minor marks on the left side of the stock, and I put up two pictures of the left side showing them. A little buffing and then adding some  tung oil to the finish would probably take care of it. These rifles are $450 or more new. This one is $315. The only reason I am selling it is I want more money for bulding up a duck hunting boat for the fall season. It's a very well made rifle, and a great buy.

title: For Sale:  Husqvarna 1907 ( 1903 Browning)
postcontent: Under  license from Fabrique National the Swedish company Husqvarna began manufacturing the Husqvarna Model 1907 pistol in 1917 for primarily the Military forces. It remained in production until around 1940. It is the same pistol as the Browning 1903. There were also pistols made for the civilian market with the 1907 designation. When these guns were imported into the Unite States, the importers realized that the original chambering ( 9mm. Browning Long ) would not be a popular sell. There solution was to replace the original barrels with one chambered for .380 Auto, a popular cartridge in the US. The side of the frame was then stamped ".380 Auto". Everything except the barrel stayed the same. The pistol I have for sale has the Military Regiment desination stamped on the left side of the frame. I'm guessing this gun was made sometime in the early 1920's, but I'm not sure. In my pictures you will see a second barrel, that is the .380 barrel installed for US sale and is chambered in .380 Auto. Installed in the gun is a factory Browning 9mm. Long barrel. So you can shoot both .380 Auto and the 9mm. Browning Long cartridges from this pistol. It only requires changing the barrel. I will include some Browning 9mm. Long ammo with this sale. Both barrels have excellent bores. Any questions just email. Buyer must be an Ohio Resident and be at least 21 years of age. Thanks for looking.

title: For Sale/Trade:  CZ-75B 9mm with RARE Kadet2 Slide .22LR
postcontent: CZ-75B in 9mm plus Kadet2 slide in .22LR.  This sale is for one (1) frame and two (2) slides.  The gunsmiths of the Czech Republic are world renowned for their skills and designs; they have to be, they are a small, technologically advanced society surrounded by large and often unfriendly neighbors!  The CZ-75 may be considered one of the finest 9mm pistols in history.  It features a DA/SA system, with the first shot taken either DA and the follow on shots SA, or it can be carried "Cocked and Locked" like a 1911 for a fast SA first and SA follow-on shots.  Col. Jeff Cooper admired the CZ as one of the few "wonder-nines" because of the designs' ability to be carried "Cocked and Locked".The Kadet2 Adapter is a unique and very rare piece of kit.  Designed to allow for frequent pistol practice with the ergonomics and weight of the full sized gun, but using cheaper .22LR ammo.  Unlike some other .22LR adapter systems that are made of lightweight potmetal, the Kadet2 is full steel with a unique slide system.  It utilizes the same trigger pull, hammer drop, frame, weight, and ergodynamics of the CZ in the .22LR.  A picture below shows the Kadet2 slide Open.The Kadet2 is not widely imported by CZ into the US.  Finding one is expensive, if you can find one at all.  Finding a Kadet2 used is even rarer as folks don't usually let go of a Kadet2 once they have it.  Finding a Kadet2 that is precision matched to the frame is the rarest of all CZ finds.  I purchased the CZ-75B and Kadet2 new, and I hand fit the Kadet2 to the frame by carefully shaving away mere thousandths of an inch on all the bearing parts until the Kadet2 fit perfectly.  The fit is tight, firm, and allows for amazing accuracy.The Kadet2 comes with a micro adjustable rear sight.  I added the same sight to the 9mm slide.  Both are adjusted such that CCI MaxiMag .22LR HyperVelocity and Hornady American Gunner 115gr 9mm +P both print with the same accuracy at 7 yards.  This allows for lots of practice with reduced recoil of the .22LR, and then switching over the slide to 9mm for carry or competition.What comes with this package:1 ea. CZ-75B steel frame1 ea. CZ-75B 9mm slide1 ea. Kadet2 Adapter Slide .22LR2 ea. 9mm magazines at 16 +1.  I replaced the standard steel baseplates with CZ rubber baseplates, the steel plates are included in the package and shown in the pictures.2 ea. .22LR magazines at 10 + 12 ea. frame pins, one for .22LR, one for 9mm, but either works with either slide2 ea. custom boxes, one for the 9mm, one for the Kadet21 ea. 9mm patch jag and 9mm bore brush1 ea. .22LR patch jag and .22LR bore brush2 ea. plastic standard CZ grips (never used-shown in pictures)2 ea. custom smooth brushed aluminum CZ grips - mounted on the frame as shown1 ea. combat rear sight (part of the three dot sighting system) that can be reinstalled into either slide dovetail.  Shown in pictures.1 ea. Galco Black leather OWB paddle holster with snap over the rear of the pistol.All the manuals and factory target sheets (shown under the pistols in the pictures).No warranties implied or expressed.  Subject to prior sale.  Sales only to Georgia Residents with a valid Georgia Driver's License, and I prefer but don't require a CCW permit.  Cash only, or trade for a comparable quality AR 15/M4 platform in .223REM/5.56NATO with a quality optic system.  Show me what you have!A chance to own one of the finest 9mm's made, lightly used, well cared for PLUS the ultra rare Kadet2 Adapter Slide custom fitted to the frame.txt: nine one twofour two nineone nine seven one
